{"type":"route","meta":{"status":200,"headers":{"content-type":"application/rss+xml; charset=utf-8","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/rss/layout,_N_T_/rss/route,_N_T_/rss"}},"body":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<rss version=\"2.0\" xmlns:atom=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\">\n  <channel>\n    <title>The Breakdown</title>\n    <link>https://thebreakdown.in</link>\n    <description>Independent, data-driven journalism on Indian policy, politics, and society.</description>\n    <language>en-in</language>\n    <atom:link href=\"https://thebreakdown.in/rss\" rel=\"self\" type=\"application/rss+xml\"/>\n    \n    <item>\n      <title>India-Russia: The Enduring Partnership Tested by War and Realignment</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-russia-relations</link>\n      <description>India's oldest strategic partnership is navigating the Ukraine war, a dramatic surge in oil imports, Western sanctions pressure, and Russia's deepening embrace of China — all while defence dependency keeps the relationship anchored.</description>\n      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-russia-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India-UK Relations: Beyond Colonial History to a Modern Strategic Partnership</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-uk-relations</link>\n      <description>The India-UK relationship has reinvented itself through a Comprehensive Strategic Partnership, FTA negotiations, and robust diaspora links — but difficult conversations on historical reparations, migration, and trade-offs persist.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-uk-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India and Europe: A Strategic Partnership Searching for Substance</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-europe-relations</link>\n      <description>As the EU seeks to diversify away from China and India looks West for technology and investment, the India-EU strategic partnership is gaining momentum — but trade negotiations, carbon policy, and differing worldviews on Russia remain obstacles.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 22 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-europe-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India-China: Two Asian Giants in an Era of Mistrust and Strategic Rivalry</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-china-relations</link>\n      <description>From the Galwan Valley clash to a widening trade deficit and competition across the Indian Ocean, the India-China relationship has reached its most volatile point since the 1962 war.</description>\n      <pubDate>Thu, 20 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-china-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India-Indonesia: How Maritime Neighbours Are Reshaping the Indo-Pacific</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-indonesia-relations</link>\n      <description>India and Indonesia share 2,000 years of civilisational links and are now deepening a Comprehensive Strategic Partnership focused on maritime security, trade, and countering Chinese influence in Southeast Asia.</description>\n      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-indonesia-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India-US Relations: From Nuclear Deal to Critical Technology Partnership</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-us-relations</link>\n      <description>The India-US strategic partnership has deepened across defence, technology, trade, and people-to-people ties over the past two decades, driven by shared concerns about China's rise and converging geopolitical interests.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Aug 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-us-relations</guid>\n      <category>geopolitics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India's EV Paradox: Rising Sales, Stalled Charging, and the ₹4 Lakh Crore Battery Import Bill</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-ev-paradox</link>\n      <description>EV sales have grown 4x in three years, but India's public charging network stands at only 26% of the official target. Meanwhile, the country's battery import bill is projected to hit ₹4 lakh crore by 2030 — creating a strategic vulnerability as deep as the oil dependency EVs were meant to solve.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-ev-paradox</guid>\n      <category>environment</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Electoral Bonds: The ₹12,769 Crore Anonymous Donation Scheme the Supreme Court Struck Down</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/electoral-bonds</link>\n      <description>Electoral Bonds were meant to clean up political funding. Instead, they created the most opaque campaign finance system in Indian history — ₹12,769 crore in anonymous donations, 47.5% flowing to the BJP, with shell companies and contractors under investigation pouring ₹4,200+ crore into ruling party coffers. The Supreme Court struck down the scheme in February 2024.</description>\n      <pubDate>Fri, 14 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/electoral-bonds</guid>\n      <category>policy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India's 5G Revolution: 400 Million Subscribers and Still Waiting for the Killer App</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-5g-rollout</link>\n      <description>India crossed 40 crore 5G subscribers in mid-2026 — the fastest 5G rollout by volume globally — but enterprise adoption remains tepid, average revenue per user is stagnant at sub-₹200, only 40% of towers are fiberized, and the industry awaits the breakthrough application that will justify the ₹5 lakh crore capital expenditure.</description>\n      <pubDate>Wed, 12 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-5g-rollout</guid>\n      <category>technology</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Ayushman Bharat: India's ₹30,000 Crore Bet on Universal Health Coverage</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ayushman-bharat</link>\n      <description>Ayushman Bharat Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (AB-PMJAY) has become the world's largest publicly funded health insurance scheme, covering 12.5 crore families and facilitating 6.2 crore hospitalizations in eight years — but questions persist about coverage gaps, hospital quality, and whether ₹30,000 crore can sustain universal health coverage for a nation of 1.4 billion.</description>\n      <pubDate>Mon, 10 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ayushman-bharat</guid>\n      <category>health</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Who Really Gets the EWS Quota? An Investigation into UPSC's 104 Selections</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ews-quota-upsc-investigation</link>\n      <description>An investigation into all 104 candidates selected under the 10% EWS quota in Civil Services 2025 finds IIT graduates, private school alumni, and business family children — raising fundamental questions about targeting and due diligence.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 08 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ews-quota-upsc-investigation</guid>\n      <category>policy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>E20 Backlash: India's Ethanol Push and the Consumer Revolt That Followed</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ethanol-backlash</link>\n      <description>India achieved 20% ethanol blending five years ahead of schedule, but motorists report mileage drops of up to 12%, the food-versus-fuel debate resurfaces, and a Supreme Court PIL challenges the rollout.</description>\n      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ethanol-backlash</guid>\n      <category>environment</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India's Foreign Policy at 80: From Non-Alignment to Multi-Alignment</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/indias-foreign-policy</link>\n      <description>As India celebrates 80 years of independence, its foreign policy has undergone a fundamental transformation — from Nehruvian idealism to pragmatic multi-alignment, balancing the US, China, Russia, and the Global South.</description>\n      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/indias-foreign-policy</guid>\n      <category>politics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>The Great Supply Chain Shift: Can India Capture the China+1 Opportunity?</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/supply-chain-shift</link>\n      <description>As global companies diversify away from China, India has attracted $85 billion in FDI since 2023 — but infrastructure gaps and policy inconsistency threaten to squander the moment.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Aug 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/supply-chain-shift</guid>\n      <category>economy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India-China at the Crossroads: Four Years After Galwan, the Border Remains the Flashpoint</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-china-border-tensions</link>\n      <description>Despite 20 rounds of military talks, India and China remain locked in the most intense border confrontation in five decades — with 60,000 troops deployed on each side and a broader strategic rivalry reshaping Asia.</description>\n      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/india-china-border-tensions</guid>\n      <category>politics</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Anganwadi Centres: India's Frontline Nutrition Workers Are Burning Out</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/anganwadi-icds</link>\n      <description>India's Integrated Child Development Services (ICDS) runs 14 lakh anganwadi centres serving 10 crore beneficiaries, but frontline workers face wage delays, infrastructure gaps, and mounting workloads.</description>\n      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/anganwadi-icds</guid>\n      <category>health</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Income Inequality in India: The Top 1% Now Owns 40% of the Wealth</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/income-inequality-india</link>\n      <description>India's income inequality has reached levels not seen since the colonial era — the top 1% holds 40% of national wealth while the bottom 50% holds just 13%. An examination of the structural drivers behind India's Gini coefficient trajectory.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/income-inequality-india</guid>\n      <category>economy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>Digitizing PDS: How Technology Plugged the Leakage in India's Food Security Net</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ration-digitization</link>\n      <description>Aadhaar seeding and ePoS deployment have reduced leakage in India's Public Distribution System from 40% to under 10%, but coverage gaps persist.</description>\n      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/ration-digitization</guid>\n      <category>economy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India's Education Paradox: Rising Enrolment, Falling Learning — What Went Wrong?</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/indian-education-crisis</link>\n      <description>While near-universal enrolment has been achieved at the primary level, India's education system faces a crisis of quality — half of Class 5 students cannot read a Class 2 textbook. An investigation into the systemic failures behind the learning poverty trap.</description>\n      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/indian-education-crisis</guid>\n      <category>policy</category>\n    </item>\n    <item>\n      <title>India's Groundwater Crisis: 62% of Districts Sound the Alarm</title>\n      <link>https://thebreakdown.in/story/groundwater-depletion</link>\n      <description>Groundwater depletion threatens India's food and water security as 62% of districts face critical or over-exploited groundwater levels, driven primarily by agricultural irrigation.</description>\n      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Jul 2026 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>\n      <guid>https://thebreakdown.in/story/groundwater-depletion</guid>\n      <category>environment</category>\n    </item>\n  </channel>\n</rss>"}